												He received his PhD in Agricultural Electrification & Automation from Nanjing Agricultural University in 2019.
												His research interests include AI for sustainable agriculture, medical imaging, responsible AI frameworks,
												and contextually-aware AI solutions for East Africa. Innocent has published 22+ research articles
												with 830+ citations and maintains active collaborations with leading universities across Australia, USA, UK, and China.
											</p>
